__NUXT_JSONP__("/archives/3", (function(a){return {data:[{posts:[{id:1724,slug:"keyboard-navigation",title:{rendered:"Keyboard navigation"},excerpt:{rendered:"\u003Cp\u003EThere are many different ways to use the web besides a mouse and a pair of eyes. Users navigate for example with a keyboard only or with their voice. All the functionality, including menus, links and forms should work using a keyboard only. This is essential for all assistive technology to work properly. The only&hellip; \u003Ca class=\"more-link\" href=\"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F2018\u002F10\u002F20\u002Fkeyboard-navigation\u002F\"\u003EContinue reading \u003Cspan class=\"screen-reader-text\"\u003EKeyboard navigation\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n",protected:a}},{id:1178,slug:"markup-html-tags-and-formatting",title:{rendered:"Markup: HTML Tags and Formatting"},excerpt:{rendered:"\u003Cp\u003EHeadings Header one Header two Header three Header four Header five Header six Blockquotes Single line blockquote: Stay hungry. Stay foolish. Multi line blockquote with a cite reference: The HTML &lt;blockquote&gt; Element (or HTML Block Quotation Element) indicates that the enclosed text is an extended quotation. Usually, this is rendered visually by indentation (see Notes&hellip; \u003Ca class=\"more-link\" href=\"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F2013\u002F01\u002F11\u002Fmarkup-html-tags-and-formatting\u002F\"\u003EContinue reading \u003Cspan class=\"screen-reader-text\"\u003EMarkup: HTML Tags and Formatting\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n",protected:a}},{id:1177,slug:"markup-image-alignment",title:{rendered:"Markup: Image Alignment"},excerpt:{rendered:"\u003Cp\u003EWelcome to image alignment! The best way to demonstrate the ebb and flow of the various image positioning options is to nestle them snuggly among an ocean of words. Grab a paddle and let&#8217;s get started. On the topic of alignment, it should be noted that users can choose from the options of None, Left,&hellip; \u003Ca class=\"more-link\" href=\"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F2013\u002F01\u002F10\u002Fmarkup-image-alignment\u002F\"\u003EContinue reading \u003Cspan class=\"screen-reader-text\"\u003EMarkup: Image Alignment\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n",protected:a}},{id:1176,slug:"markup-text-alignment",title:{rendered:"Markup: Text Alignment"},excerpt:{rendered:"\u003Cp\u003EDefault This is a paragraph. It should not have any alignment of any kind. It should just flow like you would normally expect. Nothing fancy. Just straight up text, free flowing, with love. Completely neutral and not picking a side or sitting on the fence. It just is. It just freaking is. It likes where&hellip; \u003Ca class=\"more-link\" href=\"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F2013\u002F01\u002F09\u002Fmarkup-text-alignment\u002F\"\u003EContinue reading \u003Cspan class=\"screen-reader-text\"\u003EMarkup: Text Alignment\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n",protected:a}},{id:1174,slug:"title-with-special-characters",title:{rendered:"Markup: Title With Special Characters ~`!@#$%^&#038;*()-_=+{}[]\u002F\\;:'&#8221;?,.\u003E"},excerpt:{rendered:"\u003Cp\u003EPutting special characters in the title should have no adverse effect on the layout or functionality. Special characters in the post title have been known to cause issues with JavaScript when it is minified, especially in the admin when editing the post itself (ie. issues with metaboxes, media upload, etc.). Latin Character Tests This is&hellip; \u003Ca class=\"more-link\" href=\"http:\u002F\u002Flocalhost\u002F2013\u002F01\u002F05\u002Ftitle-with-special-characters\u002F\"\u003EContinue reading \u003Cspan class=\"screen-reader-text\"\u003EMarkup: Title With Special Characters ~`!@#$%^&#038;*()-_=+{}[]\u002F\\;:&#8217;&#8221;?,.\u003E\u003C\u002Fspan\u003E\u003C\u002Fa\u003E\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n",protected:a}},{id:1173,slug:"markup-title-with-markup",title:{rendered:"Markup: Title \u003Cem\u003EWith\u003C\u002Fem\u003E \u003Cb\u003EMark\u003Csup\u003Eup\u003C\u002Fsup\u003E\u003C\u002Fb\u003E"},excerpt:{rendered:"\u003Cp\u003EVerify that: The post title renders the word &#8220;with&#8221; in italics and the word &#8220;markup&#8221; in bold (and &#8220;up&#8221; is superscript). The post title markup should be removed from the browser window \u002F tab.\u003C\u002Fp\u003E\n",protected:a}}],pages:9}],fetch:{},mutations:void 0}}(false)));